Absa Group, Adcock Ingram and Anglo American: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-04-20T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/absa-group-adcock-ingram-anglo-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index increased for a second
day, rallying 689.24, or 2.2 percent, to 32,526.30 by the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.  Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  : South Africa’s largest retail
Bank holds a  shareholders’ meeting . The stock rose 5.10 rand, or
3.9 percent, to 137.50 rand.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  : The diversified mining company
that makes up 11 percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock index
releases a first-quarter production update. The company also
holds a shareholders’ meeting. Anglo climbed 9.30 rand, or 2.7
percent, to 352 rand.  Adcock Ingram Holdings Ltd. (AIP)  : The drugs supplier
said in a statement that it will appeal a decision by the
Medicines Control Council to withdraw the registration of
dextropropoxyphene-containing medicines from the South African
market. The stock rose 11 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 57.55 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
